 pose tough questions about the existing market economy and the movement towards globalization. They challenge neoliberalism's absolute faith in market solutions and present a strong case for humane public intervention to ensure that increases in wealth are directed to fulfilling the highest potential for all humankind. This book should prove stimulating for readers of all political faiths.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aSocialism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh1 aArias, Oscar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBannon, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBroadbent, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlsson, Ingvar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEppler, Erhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKinnock, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLange, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeres, Shimon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRae, Bob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRocard, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRussell, Peter H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRussell, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148758338540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487583385423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487583385.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-19